    {'id':'y2-t4-w3-l3','year':'Y2','term':'T4',     'week':3,'weekLesson':3,     'sequence':'Sequence 10','lesson':'Lesson 1',     'focus':'Doubling consonants when adding suffixes',     'explanation':'This rule is complex because it contains several considerations and skills:\n1.\nThe number of syllables in the word\n2.\nThe final two letters of the word\n3.\nKnowledge of vowels and consonants\n4.\nKnowledge of vowel suffixes\nFor the purposes of vowel suffix rules, the letter ‘y’ is considered a vowel when applied as a suffix.\nWhen a word with one syllable ends in a single short vowel + consonant, we double the consonant before \nadding the vowel suffix (-ed/-ing/-er/-est/-y).\nFor example, the word jump ends in consonant + consonant.\nTherefore, we do not double the consonant (e.g. jumped or jumping',     'hlWords':['evil', 'civil', 'stencil', 'utensil', 'muscle', 'devil', 'fossil', 'nostril', 'basil', 'pupil']},
    {'id':'y2-t4-w3-l4','year':'Y2','term':'T4',     'week':3,'weekLesson':4,     'sequence':'Sequence 10','lesson':'Lesson 2',     'focus':'Doubling consonants when adding suffixes',     'explanation':'This rule is complex because it contains several considerations and skills:\n1.\nThe number of syllables in the word\n2.\nThe final two letters of the word\n3.\nKnowledge of vowels and consonants\n4.\nKnowledge of vowel suffixes\nFor the purposes of vowel suffix rules, the letter ‘y’ is considered a vowel when applied as a suffix.\nWhen a word with one syllable ends in a single short vowel + consonant, we double the consonant before \nadding the vowel suffix (-ed/-ing/-er/-est/-y).\nFor example, the word jump ends in consonant + consonant.\nTherefore, we do not double the consonant (e.g. jumped or jumping',     'hlWords':['boys', 'keys', 'plays', 'stays', 'monkeys', 'enjoys', 'delays', 'ways', 'buys', 'toys']},
