    {'id':'y3-t2-w3-l1','year':'Y3','term':'T2',     'week':3,'weekLesson':1,     'sequence':'Sequence 2','lesson':'Lesson 1',     'focus':'adding the -ly suffix',     'explanation':'For most root words, we simply add the -ly suffix (because it begins with a consonant).\nHowever, there are some exceptions to this, where other rules apply.\nIf the root word ends in y, change y to i before adding -ly.\nFor example, the word happy becomes happily.\nIf the root word ends in -le, change -le to -ly.\nFor example, the word gentle becomes gently.\nIf the root word ends in -ic, use the -ally suffix (instead of -ly).\nFor example, the word magic becomes magically.',     'hlWords':['quickly', 'slowly', 'kindly', 'sadly', 'nicely', 'softly', 'loudly', 'bravely', 'closely', 'nearly']},
