    {'id':'y3-t4-w1-l1','year':'Y3','term':'T4',     'week':1,'weekLesson':1,     'sequence':'Sequence 4','lesson':'Lesson 1',     'focus':'words ending -sion',     'explanation':'The -sion ending is applied to verbs to form nouns.\nThe -sion ending sounds like zh-un.\nWhen a verb ends in se, we can remove se and replace it with sion.\nFor example, the verb confuse can be used to form the noun confusion.\nWhen a verb ends in de, we can remove de and replace it with sion.\nFor example, the verb decide can be used to form the noun decision.',     'hlWords':['version', 'confusion', 'revision', 'fusion', 'television', 'decision', 'invasion', 'conclusion', 'erosion', 'diffusion']},
