    {'id':'y3-t4-w2-l1','year':'Y3','term':'T4',     'week':2,'weekLesson':1,     'sequence':'Sequence 5','lesson':'Lesson 1',     'focus':'short i sound spelled y',     'explanation':'Within some words, the short i sound is represented by the letter y.\n(This is not the case at the end of words.)\nThere is no spelling rule for words containing the short i sound spelled y.\nInstead, these words simply have to be learned.\nHowever, there are some useful patterns.\nFor example, the short i sound spelled y often appears after the letter s at the beginning of a word.\nIn addition, it often precedes or follows the letter m.',     'hlWords':['pyramid', 'myth', 'crystal', 'lyrics', 'rhythm', 'syllable', 'symptom', 'synonym', 'system', 'symmetry']},
