    {'id':'y4-t4-w4-l1','year':'Y4','term':'T4',     'week':4,'weekLesson':1,     'sequence':'Sequence 6','lesson':'Lesson 1',     'focus':'prefixes',     'explanation':'Prefixes are units of meaning added to the beginning of a root word in order to change its meaning.\nThe re- prefix usually means again.\nFor example, the word rewrite means to write again.\nIt can, in some cases, mean back.\nFor example, the word retreat means to move back.\nThe sub- prefix means under.\nFor example, the word subheading means a heading underneath the main heading.\nThese prefixes are usually added with no change to the root word.',     'hlWords':['submarine', 'reschedule', 'reprint', 'subheading', 'redecorate', 'submerge', 'rewrite', 'reappear', 'subway', 'rebuild']},
    {'id':'y4-t4-w4-l2','year':'Y4','term':'T4',     'week':4,'weekLesson':2,     'sequence':'Sequence 6','lesson':'Lesson 2',     'focus':'prefixes',     'explanation':'Prefixes are units of meaning added to the beginning of a root word in order to change its meaning.\nThe super- prefix means above or beyond.\nIt is used to show that something is better than or superior to something else.\nFor example, the word superglue means glue that is above or better/stronger than other glue.\nThe inter- prefix means between.\nFor example, the word intercity means something is happening between more than one city.\nThese prefixes are usually added with no change to the root word.',     'hlWords':['intercity', 'internet', 'international', 'superhero', 'supermarket', 'superglue', 'superpower', 'superstar', 'interlink', 'interact']},
    {'id':'y4-t4-w4-l3','year':'Y4','term':'T4',     'week':4,'weekLesson':3,     'sequence':'Sequence 6','lesson':'Lesson 3',     'focus':'prefixes',     'explanation':'Prefixes are units of meaning added to the beginning of a root word in order to change its meaning.\nThe anti- prefix means against or the opposite.\nFor example, the word antigravity means a force that works against gravity.\nThe auto- prefix means self or own.\nFor example, the word autobiography means a biography (life story) written about yourself.\nThese prefixes are usually added with no change to the root word.',     'hlWords':['antisocial', 'antifreeze', 'antihero', 'anticlockwise', 'antivirus', 'autograph', 'autobiography', 'autopilot', 'autocorrect', 'automatic']},
    {'id':'y4-t4-w5-l1','year':'Y4','term':'T4',     'week':5,'weekLesson':1,     'sequence':'Sequence 6','lesson':'Lesson 4',     'focus':'prefixes',     'explanation':'Prefixes are units of meaning added to the beginning of a root word in order to change its meaning.\nThe re- prefix usually means again.\nIt can, in some cases, mean back.\nThe sub- prefix means under.\nThe super- prefix means above or beyond.\nIt is used to show that something is better than or superior to something else.\nThe inter- prefix means between.\nThe anti- prefix means against or the opposite.\nThe auto- prefix means self or own.\nThese prefixes are usually added with no change to the root word.',     'hlWords':['superman', 'reappear', 'antigravity', 'subtitle', 'interlink', 'autograph', 'superglue', 'subheading', 'antifreeze', 'antisocial']},
