    {'id':'y4-t5-w4-l1','year':'Y4','term':'T5',     'week':4,'weekLesson':1,     'sequence':'Sequence 8','lesson':'Lesson 1',     'focus':'the -ation suffix',     'explanation':'The -ation suffix is usually used to turn a verb into a noun.\nFor example, the verb inform becomes information (noun).\nFor most words ending in a consonant, the -ation suffix is simply applied.\nFor example, the word adapt becomes adaptation.\nWhen the root words end in e, remove the e before applying the -ation suffix.\nFor example, the word prepare becomes preparation.',     'hlWords':['foundation', 'formation', 'relaxation', 'plantation', 'alteration', 'confrontation', 'consideration', 'information', 'expectation', 'affirmation']},
