    {'id':'y4-t5-w5-l1','year':'Y4','term':'T5',     'week':5,'weekLesson':1,     'sequence':'Sequence 9','lesson':'Lesson 1',     'focus':'uh spelled ou',     'explanation':'This sequence focuses on words containing the uh (/ʌ/) sound spelled ou.\nThese words do not follow a clear spelling rule. \nInstead, they simply have to be learned.\nHowever, this sequence explores common placement of the uh sound spelled ou.\nFor example, the uh sound spelled ou sometimes appears after the letter c.\nExample words include couple, country, cousin and courage.\nSimilarly, the uh sound spelled ou sometimes appears before ble/ple at the end of a word.\nExample words include couple, double and trouble.',     'hlWords':['young', 'touch', 'double', 'cousin', 'couple', 'country', 'trouble', 'courage', 'nourish', 'flourish']},
